article.headline: Sacramento State 64, Weber State 61
article.story: SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) -- Joseth Dawson scored a career-high 32 points to lead Sacramento State to a 64-61 victory over Weber State on Thursday night in the Big Sky Conference. Dawson scored Sacramento State's last 12 points, including four free throws in the final 41 seconds, to help the Hornets (11-13, 5-6) beat the Wildcats for the first time in 19 tries dating to 1969. Dawson was 5-of-9 from 3-point range and 9-of-18 overall. Dawson's 3-pointer with 1:32 left put Sacramento State up 60-56. Weber State guard John Hamilton's 3-pointer 30 seconds later cut it to 60-59, but Dawson sealed the victory at the line. Nic Sparrow led Weber State (11-13, 4-7) with 16 points, and Hamilton added 15.
